quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  26,176,The inhabitants of the thicket denied the messengers
  26,177,"when Shu?ayb said unto them, “Will you not be reverent"
  26,178,Truly I am a trustworthy messenger unto you
  26,179,So reverence God and obey me
  26,180,And I ask not of you any reward for it; my reward lies only with the Lord of the worlds
  26,181,"Give full measure, and be not among those who fall short"
  26,182,Weigh with the right balance
  26,183,"and diminish not people’s goods, nor behave wickedly upon the earth, working corruption"
  26,184,And reverence Him Who created you and the generations of old.”
  26,185,"They said, “You are but one of the bewitched"
  26,186,"You are naught but a human being like us, and indeed we deem you to be among the liars"
  26,187,"so make fragments from the sky fall upon us, if you are among the truthful.”"
  26,188,"He said, “My Lord knows best what you do.”"
  26,189,"So they denied him, and the punishment of the day of gloom seized them. Truly it was the punishment of a tremendous day"
  26,190,"Truly in that is a sign, but most of them are not believers"
  26,191,"And truly thy Lord is indeed the Mighty, the Merciful"